Document: AccessibilityServer  
Path: godot/classes/class_accessibilityserver.rst  
Summary: Enumerations and constants for accessibility roles, popup types, flags, actions, live modes, scroll units, and scroll hints in the AccessibilityServer class.  

AccessibilityRole (int):  
- ROLE_UNKNOWN: Unknown or custom role.  
- ROLE_DEFAULT_BUTTON: Default dialog button element.  
- ROLE_AUDIO: Audio player element.  
- ROLE_VIDEO: Video player element.  
- ROLE_STATIC_TEXT: Non-editable text label.  
- ROLE_CONTAINER: Container element. Elements with this role are used for internal structure and ignored by screen readers.  
- ROLE_PANEL: Panel container element.  
- ROLE_BUTTON: Button element.  
- ROLE_LINK: Link element.  
- ROLE_CHECK_BOX: Check box element.  
- ROLE_RADIO_BUTTON: Radio button element.  
- ROLE_CHECK_BUTTON: Check button element.  
- ROLE_SCROLL_BAR: Scroll bar element.  
- ROLE_SCROLL_VIEW: Scroll container element.  
- ROLE_SPLITTER: Container splitter handle element.  
- ROLE_SLIDER: Slider element.  
- ROLE_SPIN_BUTTON: Spin box element.  
- ROLE_PROGRESS_INDICATOR: Progress indicator element.  
- ROLE_TEXT_FIELD: Editable text field element.  
- ROLE_MULTILINE_TEXT_FIELD: Multiline editable text field element.  
- ROLE_COLOR_PICKER: Color picker element.  
- ROLE_TABLE: Table element.  
- ROLE_CELL: Table/tree cell element.  
- ROLE_ROW: Table/tree row element.  
- ROLE_ROW_GROUP: Table/tree row group element.  
- ROLE_ROW_HEADER: Table/tree row header element.  
- ROLE_COLUMN_HEADER: Table/tree column header element.  
- ROLE_TREE: Tree view element.  
- ROLE_TREE_ITEM: Tree view item element.  
- ROLE_LIST: List element.  
- ROLE_LIST_ITEM: List item element.  
- ROLE_LIST_BOX: List view element.  
- ROLE_LIST_BOX_OPTION: List view item element.  
- ROLE_TAB_BAR: Tab bar element.  
- ROLE_TAB: Tab bar item element.  
- ROLE_TAB_PANEL: Tab panel element.  
- ROLE_MENU_BAR: Menu bar element.  
- ROLE_MENU: Popup menu element.  
- ROLE_MENU_ITEM: Popup menu item element.  
- ROLE_MENU_ITEM_CHECK_BOX: Popup menu check button item element.  
- ROLE_MENU_ITEM_RADIO: Popup menu radio button item element.  
- ROLE_IMAGE: Image element.  
- ROLE_WINDOW: Window element.  
- ROLE_TITLE_BAR: Embedded window title bar element.  
- ROLE_DIALOG: Dialog window element.  
- ROLE_TOOLTIP: Tooltip element.  
- ROLE_REGION: Region/landmark element. Screen readers can navigate between regions using landmark navigation.  
- ROLE_TEXT_RUN: Unifor text run. Note: This role is used for internal text elements, and should not be assigned to nodes.  

AccessibilityPopupType (int):  
- POPUP_MENU: Popup menu.  
- POPUP_LIST: Popup list.  
- POPUP_TREE: Popup tree view.  
- POPUP_DIALOG: Popup dialog.  

AccessibilityFlags (int):  
- FLAG_HIDDEN: Element is hidden for accessibility tools.  
- FLAG_MULTISELECTABLE: Element supports multiple item selection.  
- FLAG_REQUIRED: Element requires user input.  
- FLAG_VISITED: Element is a visited link.  
- FLAG_BUSY: Element content is not ready (e.g. loading).  
- FLAG_MODAL: Element is modal window.  
- FLAG_TOUCH_PASSTHROUGH: Element allows touches to be passed through when a screen reader is in touch exploration mode.  
- FLAG_READONLY: Element is text field with selectable but read-only text.  
- FLAG_DISABLED: Element is disabled.  
- FLAG_CLIPS_CHILDREN: Element clips children.  

AccessibilityAction (int):  
- ACTION_CLICK: Single click action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_FOCUS: Focus action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_BLUR: Blur action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_COLLAPSE: Collapse action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_EXPAND: Expand action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_DECREMENT: Decrement action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_INCREMENT: Increment action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_HIDE_TOOLTIP: Hide tooltip action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_SHOW_TOOLTIP: Show tooltip action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_SET_TEXT_SELECTION: Set text selection action, callback argument is set to Dictionary with keys: "start_element", "start_char", "end_element", "end_char".  
- ACTION_REPLACE_SELECTED_TEXT: Replace text action, callback argument is set to String with the replacement text.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_BACKWARD: Scroll backward action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_DOWN: Scroll down action, callback argument is set to AccessibilityScrollUnit.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_FORWARD: Scroll forward action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_LEFT: Scroll left action, callback argument is set to AccessibilityScrollUnit.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_RIGHT: Scroll right action, callback argument is set to AccessibilityScrollUnit.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_UP: Scroll up action, callback argument is set to AccessibilityScrollUnit.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_INTO_VIEW: Scroll into view action, callback argument is set to AccessibilityScrollHint.  
- ACTION_SCROLL_TO_POINT: Scroll to point action, callback argument is set to Vector2 with relative point coordinates.  
- ACTION_SET_SCROLL_OFFSET: Set scroll offset action, callback argument is set to Vector2 with scroll offset.  
- ACTION_SET_VALUE: Set value action, callback argument is set to String or number with the new value.  
- ACTION_SHOW_CONTEXT_MENU: Show context menu action, callback argument is not set.  
- ACTION_CUSTOM: Custom action, callback argument is set to the integer action ID.  

AccessibilityLiveMode (int):  
- LIVE_OFF: Indicates that updates to the live region should not be presented.  
- LIVE_POLITE: Indicates that updates to the live region should be presented at the next opportunity.  
- LIVE_ASSERTIVE: Indicates that updates to the live region have the highest priority and should be presented immediately.  

AccessibilityScrollUnit (int):  
- SCROLL_UNIT_ITEM: Scroll amount: a single item of a list, line of text.  
- SCROLL_UNIT_PAGE: Scroll amount: a single page.  

AccessibilityScrollHint (int):  
- SCROLL_HINT_TOP_LEFT: Preferred position: top-left edge of the scroll container.  
- SCROLL_HINT_BOTTOM_RIGHT: Preferred position: bottom-right edge of the scroll container.  
- SCROLL_HINT_TOP_EDGE: Preferred position: top edge of the scroll container.  
- SCROLL_HINT_BOTTOM_EDGE: Preferred position: bottom edge of the scroll container.  
- SCROLL_HINT_LEFT_EDGE: Preferred position: left edge of the scroll container.  
- SCROLL_HINT_RIGHT_EDGE: Preferred position: right edge of the scroll container.
